<PageTitle>Blink - Privacy</PageTitle>

<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
<p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> June 8, 2025</p>

<h2>1. Data We Collect</h2>
<p>Blink stores:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Game scores and points (e.g., Wordle)</li>
    <li>Server activity stats (e.g., voice time, cam usage, etc.)</li>
    <li>Basic command usage data</li>
</ul>
<p>This is tied only to your Discord user ID (a numeric ID), which is not personally identifiable.</p>

<p>We <strong>do not</strong> collect message content, IP addresses, or any sensitive personal data.</p>

<h2>2. How We Use Data</h2>
<p>We use this data to power bot features like leaderboards, gameplay, and activity tracking.</p>

<h2>3. Third-Party Services</h2>
<p>Blink uses a dictionary API to retrieve word definitions. No user data is shared with it.</p>

<h2>4. Your Rights</h2>
<p>You may request your data or ask us to delete it. Contact the developer via Discord: <code>EpicOfficer</code>.
    Requests are handled manually.</p>

<h2>5. Security</h2>
<p>Data is securely stored on our hosting platform, but we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>